      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Brown the butter and make the batter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt the {{unsalted-butter}} in a small saucepan over medium heat. Continue cooking until the solids on the base turn deep amber and smell nutty, about 5 minutes. Pour into a bowl and cool to room temperature.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk together the {{almond-flour}}, {{icing-sugar}}, and {{plain-flour}} in a large bowl. Stir in the egg whites from {{eggs}} and {{vanilla-extract}} until smooth. Pour in the cooled brown butter and mix until fully incorporated. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 12 to 14 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 190°C fan. Butter a 12-hole mini muffin tin generously. Fill each hole three-quarters full with batter. Bake for 12 to 14 minutes, until the tops are deep gold at the edges and set in the centre when pressed lightly. Cool in the tin for 3 minutes, then ease out with a small palette knife.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
